  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Experiments were performed across five flow-speed operating points; validation results were collected and compared against physical measurements. Some results carry full provenance; others were recorded from legacy test campaigns and the originating activity record was not captured in the structured evidence package. This package is accepted at Low assurance for the purposes of demonstrating the credibility framework, but the missing generation activity links represent an epistemic gap flagged under W-EP-02.",
